author: Inside Edition
description: Christopher Scholtes, who pled guilty after leaving his 2-year-old daughter in a hot car, committed suicide, authorities say. Scholtes was found dead in his home in Arizona. Police are investigating but won't say how he apparently killed himself. The 28-year-old was due to turn himself in on Wednesday to start his sentence but he never showed up. Inside Edition spoke to Lindsay Eisenberg, the former legal guardian to Scholtes' daughter from a previous relationship.
title: Father Who Pled Guilty After Leaving Kid In Car Found Dead In Home

author: Inside Edition
description: New York City's first Democratic Socialist mayor, Zohran Mamdani, took aim at President Donald Trump minutes after his historic victory. Trump responded moments later, saying, "and so it begins." The New York results, as well as victories of Democratic candidates for governor of New Jersey and Virginia, are sending shock waves across the United States. Along with a new mayor, New York has a new first lady. Rama Duwaji is of Syrian descent and met her husband on the dating app Hinge.
title: Zohran Mamdani Takes Aim At President Trump After NYC Mayoral Win

author: Inside Edition
description: A police officer in pursuit of a shoplifting suspect was out of luck after the accused thief jumped into a getaway car. A woman driving by saw what was happening and asked if he wanted to get in her car. The cop and his civilian crime-fighting partner went after the car. The cop arrested the shoplifting suspect and the accused getaway driver. Inside Edition spoke to mother-of-three Lesli Smith and Sergeant Jeffrey Kahrs after she was honored by police at a ceremony in Slidell, Louisiana.
title: Woman Offers Ride To Cop Chasing Shoplifting Suspect

author: Inside Edition
description: Charlie Kirk's widow, Erika, sat down for her first tv interview since her husband's assassination. She told Fox News host Jesse Watters she wanted to see Charlie's lifeless body in the hospital. "We walked into that room, he had this smirk on his face. That smirk, that smirk to me is that look of 'you thought you could stop what I've built,'" Erika said. Erika Kirk's full interview airs Wednesday night on "Jesse Watters Primetime" on Fox News Channel.
title: Erika Kirk Sits Down For 1st TV Interview Since Husband's Murder

author: Inside Edition
description: Tom Brady's decision to clone his dog is sparking debate over cloning pets. The NFL legend revealed that his dog Lua, who died in 2023, now has a clone named Junie. Side-by-side, Brady's original pitbull mix looks identical to his new cloned pet. Now, PETA is also criticizing Brady's decision to clone. Cloning pets is a growing phenomenon. Dr. Timnah Lee, a veterinarian at the Tribeca Soho and Seaport Animal Hospital, spoke with Inside Edition.
title: NFL Legend Tom Brady Receives Backlash After Cloning His Dog

author: Inside Edition
description: Authorities say there’s been a wave of storage unit thefts taking place at facilities across the country. Portland, Oregon, resident Charles Lewis says thieves made off with $75,000 in equipment after breaking into his storage unit twice in 24 hours. Abby Heitner says thieves repeatedly robbed her unit in Colorado, stealing everything she owned in the course of a week. INSIDE EDITION shares tips to help protect your belongings.
title: Just How Safe Is Your Storage Unit?

author: Inside Edition
description: A cup of joe at a cafe in Dubai costs almost a year's worth of Starbucks. Julith Coffee claims to sell the most expensive cup of coffee in the world, made from beans they purchased at auction from Panama. They say they dropped $600,000 on 44 pounds of the rare hand picked beans. So to make back their money they're charging $1,000 per cup. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Cafe In Dubai Sells Most Expensive Coffee At $1,000 Per Cup

author: Inside Edition
description: Over a century after it sank, the Titanic continues to fascinate – and sell. England's Henry Aldridge & Son is helping auction a collection of items from Frederick Sutton, a first class passenger on the doomed ocean liner. Sutton's body was never recovered, but some of his personal effects were pulled from the water. Those effects include a canvas bag. Auctioneer Andrew Aldridge tells Inside Edition Digital something recently was found in the bag: a First Class passenger list.
title: Only Copy Of Titanic First Class Passenger List Found In Canvas Bag

author: Inside Edition
description: When a couple crashed their car driving 95 mph, police initially thought it was an accident. But investigators say when the passenger, Daniel Waterman, woke up from a coma, he told them that wasn’t the case — and accused his girlfriend, Leigha Mumby, of trying to kill him.
title: Man Wakes From Coma To Accuse Girlfriend Of Causing Crash #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: It wasn't much like the heist at the Louvre, but authorities in California are still taking it seriously. The Oakland Police Department and the FBI released video of suspects they say were involved in a break-in and burglary of a storage facility used by the Oakland Museum of California. Investigators say thieves made off with more than a thousand items which include Native American artifacts as well as laptops and other electronics. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 1,000 Items Stolen From Museum's Storage Facility in California

author: Inside Edition
description: The most famous red carpet gown is back. Supermodel Amber Valletta wore the iconic Versace jungle-print dress, made famous by Jennifer Lopez 25 years ago.
title: J.Lo's Versace Jungle-Print Dress Is Back #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Ron Dailey went on a solo hunting trip in the Sierra National Forest, where he says he took a wrong trail and a storm covered his truck under two feet of snow.
title: How Hiker Survived Weeks Lost In Wilderness #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Authorities in Florida say a deputy killed a suspect who barricaded himself in a bedroom and held his little brother at knifepoint. The Hillsborough County Sheriff's Office says they were called by the sister of the suspect. When deputies arrived, they ordered the 27-year-old suspect to send the child out of the room, while the victim could be heard begging for help. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Suspect Holding Knife To 7-Year-Old Brother's Throat Shot Dead By Deputy

author: Inside Edition
description: Sheriff’s department records show that 47-year-old Angelynn Mock is accused of first degree murder and is being held on a million dollars bond.
title: Former TV News Anchor Accused Of Killing Her Own Mother #shorts
